author: AF Williams
title: Worked well
content: These worked well for us on a recent trip.  We were in and out of the pool and ocean.  We never had an issue with getting water inside the pouch.  The only issue we had was with using the phone camera while in the pouch and while it was wet.  The outside would have water droplets on it and they would cause a photo to be blurry or show the drops.  This is understandable. I only mention it so you would think ahead if you use them.  We did find that one of the knobs came out of the holder.  This is part of what keeps the pouch closed.  We were concerned it would make it NOT waterproof any longer but that is NOT the result.  The pouch still worked fine.  I think these are a great solution for being around water and wanting to protect your phone or any small valuables.  The price is fair.  We have used them several times and they are still working well.

author: CMSA
title: Does more than just keep phones dry!
content: I bought this set for my wife and I to take hiking.  We have been several times and it always seems to rain on us and we like to take pictures in Rocky Mountain National Park.  They did their job of keeping the phones dry but I also found a couple added bonuses.  First, having the lanyard on the case makes the phones easier to carry.  Instead of digging the phone out of my jacket or pocket, I hooked it up with a carabiner to my backpack strap and then tucked it in.  It was always right there, easily accessible.  Second, I found that the quality of pictures taken while the phone was in the case is just as good as the pictures taken after taking the phone out.  The cases actually made it easier to take more pictures without losing quality or exposing the phones to the elements.

title: Case is great but beware iPhone users
content: This case is great at what it’s supposed to do, protect the phone from water. Touch screen still works through the phone and camera takes good quality pictures underwater. However with recent iPhone models (mine is a 7 but same for 8 and the pluses) the home button is not an actual button and doesn’t work through the plastic case, it needs an actual finger touch to work. This made it hard to use my phone in the case. Still giving 5 stars because that is apple’s problem not the case.
